ARABIC: ءَأَنتُمْ أَنزَلْتُمُوهُ مِنَ ٱلْمُزْنِ أَمْ نَحْنُ ٱلْمُنزِلُونَ

ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_0: Is it you who sent it down from the clouds or are We the Sender?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_1: Do you send it down from the clouds, or We send it down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_2: Is it you who brought it down from the clouds or is it We Who brought it down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_3: Is it you who sent it down from the clouds or is it We who have sent it down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_4: Is it you who caused it to descend from the cloud, or is it We Who cause it to descend?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_5: Is it you who cause it to come down from Al-Muzn, or are We the Cause of it coming down
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_6: Is it you that send it down from the clouds, or are We the senders?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_7: Did you send it down from the clouds, or did We send it?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_8: Is it ye who shed it from the raincloud, or are We the Shedder?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_9: Is it you who cause it to descend from the clouds, or do We?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_10: Send it down ye from the raincloud, or are We the Sender down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_11: Is it you who bring it down from the rain cloud, or is it We who bring [it] down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_12: Do ye bring it down (in rain) from the cloud or do We?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_13: Is it you who cause it from the rainclouds to come down, or are We the Causer of it to come down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_14: Is it you that send it down from the clouds or We?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_15: Is it you who sent it down from the clouds, or are We the Sender?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_16: Is it you who brought it down from the clouds, or is it We who bring it down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_17: [56:69] Is it you who cause it to come down from the [rain] clouds (muzn is the plural of muzna) or are We the Causer of its coming down?
ENGLISH.TRANSLATION_18: (Is it ye) people of Mecca (who shed it from the rain cloud, or are We the Shedder?) Indeed, it is We Who send it down to you.
